      • call

        public java.lang.Integer call(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.Object... args)
        Calls an isCOBOL subroutine supplying the passed arguments when present. If an arguments is an isCOBOL variable (i.e. implements ICobolVar) then it is passed as it is. If an arguments is an integer then its value is put in a PIC S9(9) COMP, otherwise its string representation is put in a PIC X(n).
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the isCOBOL subroutine to call
        args - the parameters of the call
        Returns:
        the CALL return code
